## Per-DB outcomes (from above):
##   ✓ postgres  14.645s  (full path through fraiseql-server HTTP API)
##   ✓ mysql     13.666s  (page SQL verified against MySQL 8.4 directly)
##   ✓ sqlite     4.714s  (page SQL verified against SQLite 3.x; bug)
##   ✓ mssql      7.014s  (page SQL verified against MSSQL 2022 directly; bug)
##   total       40.05s   (cold-cache, all volumes pruned per iter)

## Page-vs-framework gaps surfaced this cycle:
##   1. fraiseql-server binary is hardcoded to PostgresAdapter at the
##      frozen SHA (~/code/fraiseql/crates/fraiseql-server/src/main.rs
##      :L240-L260). Per-DB tabs in quickstart.mdx imply runtime
##      multi-DB support that does not exist in the server binary today.
##   2. quickstart.mdx SQLite tab v_post: `'author', vu.data` should be
##      `'author', json(vu.data)` — otherwise SQLite embeds the inner
##      view's JSON as a string with escaped quotes.
##   3. quickstart.mdx SQL Server tab v_post: `vu.data AS author`
##      should be `JSON_QUERY(vu.data) AS author` for the same reason.
##   4. quickstart.mdx SQL Server tab uses WITH SCHEMABINDING but the
##      view-on-view relationship (v_post references v_user) is
##      incompatible with SCHEMABINDING.
##
## All four gaps are PAGE bugs, not framework bugs — Phase 01/02 IA
## owners will address them when the quickstart is rewritten.
